-- EBRD says sold remaining stake in Polish Enea
-- By Adrian Krajewski
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 07:38AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, April 10 (Reuters) - European Bank for Reconstruction and Development [EBRD.UL] said on Thursday it sold its remaining 2.5-percent stake in Polish utility Enea <ENAE.WA>, confirming an earlier Reuters report.

The bank said it found buyers for over 11 million shares in the state-controlled company "at a small discount" to their Wednesday close of 15.63 zlotys ($5.18) apiece, with Deutsche Bank as the sole bookrunner. Market sources told Reuters that buyer interest for the stake hovered at around 14.75 zlotys per share, valuing the stake at 162.3 million zlotys ($). [ID:nW8N0MG022]